      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "YELLA (2) has been very good from tougher barriers of late, finishing second two back at Newcastle before a 1.4m win after racing parked from the second line here last week. Rises a little further in grade but the good draw can see him strike again. JACKS FYRE (10) produced a far better performance when second up last time out, coming from this row for second at this circuit and distance. Has won when third-up before so could progress enough to go one better. UNIT FORTY ONE (3) led and kept going for a last-start win by 9.5 metres at this venue. Draws well enough to push forward again. LOCKITINEDDY (8) was beaten less than 2m when resuming here last week. Draws on the back line but is open to improvement.",
